summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 1276, entitled "An Ordinance authorizing the Standard Oil Company, a corporation doing business in the City of Seattle, in the State of Washington, to temporarily lay down and maintain a railroad switch track from a point where the Columbia & Puget Sound Railroad intersects South Ninth Street in the City of Seattle to the warehouse of the said Standard Oil Company, not exceeding a distance in length of two hundred feet", approved January 7, 1890.
